               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490101-name-197" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490101-name-197" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490101-name-197" type="surname" value="WESTLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490101-name-197" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>FREDERICK WESTLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. My father is a stationer, in the Strand. The prisoner came to me on Saturday, 16th Dec, a little after six o'clock, for half a quire of note-paper and two envelopes, which came to 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he offered me a half-crown—I told him it was bad, and marked it with a hammer—I asked where he came from; he did not seem able to answer me—I asked where he worked—he said, "Down the Strand"—I cut the half-crown with the scissors and put it amongst the halfpence—I took it out on Monday morning and kept it in my pocket till Wednesday, when I gave it to the policeman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490101-name-198" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490101-name-198" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490101-name-198" type="surname" value="READ"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490101-name-198" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE READ</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a butcher, of the Strand, about 150 yards from Mr. Westley's. The prisoner came to my shop about a quarter-past six o'clock on Saturday evening week for half a pound of beef-steak—he offered me a bad half-crown—I said, "Young man, it is a bad one; have you got any more of these?"—he said he had not—I chopped it into two pieces—I gave him into custody, and gave the two pieces to the policeman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490101-name-199" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490101-name-199" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490101-name-199" type="surname" value="WARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490101-name-199" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS WARD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, F</hi> 102). I took the prisoner into custody at Mr. Read's, and received from him these two pieces of broken coin, and this half-crown from Mr. Westley—I found on the prisoner two penny-pieces.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490101-name-200" type="witnessName">
